{"DOE":[{"def":"A female deer or antelope; specifically, the female of the fallow deer, of which the male is called a buck.","pos":""}],"DOEGLIC":[{"def":"Pertaining to, or obtained from, the doegling; as, doeglic acid (Chem.","pos":""}],"DOEGLING":[{"def":"The beaked whale (Balænoptera rostrata), from which doegling oil is obtained.","pos":""},{"def":"The fictitious lessee acting as plaintiff in the common-law action of ejectment, the fictitious defendant being usually denominated Richard Roe.","pos":""}],"DOER":[{"def":"An agent or attorney; a factor.","pos":""}],"DOESKIN":[{"def":"The skin of the doe.","pos":""},{"def":"A firm woolen cloth with a smooth, soft surface like a doe's skin; -- made for men's wear.","pos":""}]}